skills or the skills within your team to actually create a native application using the React

00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:31.559
native package and library. So React native is a library that is created and maintained

00:15:31.559 --> 00:15:37.359
by Facebook, and it actually allows you to create fully native applications just using

00:15:37.359 --> 00:15:43.280
the JavaScript. So let me quickly tell you how React works by itself. React creates an

00:15:43.280 --> 00:15:49.640
HTML structure within the web browser, and it is waiting for any events in the JavaScript

00:15:49.640 --> 00:15:55.440
event loop. So let's say the action is that we want to change the word world to React.

00:15:55.440 --> 00:16:01.000
What React does in the behind the scenes is creating the new version of the HTML structure

00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:06.359
that we want to apply. It checks what is the difference between those two, and it applies

00:16:06.359 --> 00:16:11.599
only the diff to the result. So you do not rerender everything. You just change one simple

00:16:11.599 --> 00:16:17.280
component within your application. Now, what is great is that when you learn React, then

00:16:17.359 --> 00:16:23.000
you will be able to use React native just right away, because it works exactly the same

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:31.359
way. It has a JavaScript event loop running on the iPad, on iPhone, on any Android device,

00:16:31.359 --> 00:16:36.799
for example, and the only thing that it does, it actually does exactly the same. It checks

00:16:36.799 --> 00:16:41.960
what has changed, and it applies the change, but it is a real native component. So to show

00:16:41.960 --> 00:16:46.479
you the final architecture that you would have in order to have such an offline solution

00:16:46.479 --> 00:16:51.440
is on the left, you have the scale architecture where you have Plumber API deployed on RStudio

